        <h2>Game Rules & Tutorial</h2>
        <div class="tutorial-container">
            <div class="tutorial-section">
                <h3>Game Overview</h3>
                <p>Each player starts with <strong>30 HP</strong> 
                    <img src="/images/lobby/fullhp.png" alt="HP Icon" class="icon"> and <strong>4 Sparks</strong> 
                    <img src="/images/lobby/cost.png" alt="Sparks Icon" class="icon">.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Players begin with <strong>8 random cards</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Each turn, the player gains <strong>2 more sparks</strong> than in the previous round.</li>
                    <li>Each turn also adds <strong>1 random card</strong> to their hand.</li>
                    <li>A random player is selected to go first.</li>
                    <li>Turn order alternates each round.</li>
                    <li>Each turn lasts <strong>30 seconds</strong> 
                        <img src="/images/l/timer.png" alt="Timer Icon" class="icon">.</li>
                    <li>Players can play up to <strong>5 cards per turn</strong>.</li>
                    <li>The turn ends automatically after 30 seconds or when the player clicks "End Turn".</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="tutorial-section">
                <h3>Combat Mechanics</h3>
                <p>At the end of each round:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Total attack power of all cards is calculated.</li>
                    <li>Total defense power of all cards is calculated.</li>
                    <li>If the opponent’s attack exceeds your defense, the difference is subtracted from your HP.</li>
                    <li>If your defense is equal or greater — no damage is taken.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="tutorial-section">
                <h3>HP Indicator Levels</h3>
                <p>The HP bar changes appearance depending on your remaining health:</p>
                <div class="hp-indicators">
                    <div>
                        <img src="/images/lobby/fullhp.png" alt="HP Full">
                        <p>HP > 20</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <img src="/images/lobby/halfhp.png" alt="HP Medium">
                        <p>HP > 10</p>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <img src="/images/lobby/lowhp.png" alt="HP Low">
                        <p>HP ≤ 10</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
